description._content:
This is a Nokia 3310 with a Hartlepool United Football Club phone cover.  Released in 2000.  It is still one of the most successful selling phones of all time.  The phone had features built in including utilities such as a calculator and stopwatch.  It also had four games including Snake II and was easily customized with interchangable covers like the one shown.

“Carry On Collecting” is a project set up by the Museum of Hartlepool to collect objects which represent everyday life in the town and beyond, from the 1950s through to the present day. The collection also attempts to represent the diversity of the people of Hartlepool over the past 60 years
